                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 326</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly<font color="#B30000"><strike> Member</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Members</i></font> Kalra<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> and Gipson</i></font><br/><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(Principal coauthor: Senator Cervantes)<br/></i></font></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>January 27, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add Section 89045.5 to the Education Code, relating to the California State University. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 326, as introduced, Kalra.
                          California State University: audits.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the California State University and its various campuses under the administration of the Trustees of the California State University. Existing law requires the trustees to establish an internal audit staff with prescribed duties, including auditing, reviewing, cost and systems analysis, analyzing, and recommending operating procedures for the university. Existing law also requires the university’s internal audit staff to perform audits, at least once every 5 years, of the activities of the university, as provided.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require an external financial audit of each campus of the California State University to be conducted at least once every 3 years. The bill would also require all audits of the California State University or any of its campuses, including audits conducted by the university’s internal audit staff,
		to be available to the public.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.693587704279198"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 89045.5 is added to the Education Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_12C1FD00-5417-4BB5-9F82-1D20C9FDDE4A"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">89045.5.</h6> (a) Notwithstanding any other law or financial audit of the California State University, an external financial audit of each campus of the California State University shall be conducted at least once every three years.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) All audits of the California State University or any campus of the California State University, including audits conducted pursuant to Section 89045 and audits conducted pursuant to subdivision (a), shall be available to the public.</div></p></div></div></div></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i></i></font></div><div align="center"><span class="CorrectionsSeparator">___________________</span></div><br/><br/><span class="CorrectionsHeading"><span class="Correction">
